			<div class="content" id="post-content-1055696">
									

<p>Well, maybe "sloppy" isn't the best term for it, but there's no structure to the end there.</p>
<p>First we've got Addendum SCP-793:XOJ1 where some researchers are trying to say this is actually safe (that is where the smiley is) and then we've got a bunch of urgent missives for help about a moving zone from someone who speaks limited English.</p>
<p>It's disjointed, contradictory, and does not add to the feeling of the piece.</p>
<p>There's just a lot of extra wording that could be pruned down and concepts that can be communicated without extra documentation. For example, there can be a tiny line about how someone on site is claiming the zone shifts to replace all that stuff at the end.</p>

